Operating system：Windows

Compiler：MinGW g++

First, create 3 folders where the source code files are. Name them "catalog", "index" and "record" respectively.
Then, compile this project with the provided makefile. 
After compiling this project, you can input MySQL commands or "execfile <file name>;" to run SQL scripts.
The mini MySQL supports searching, adding, deleting and changing records. Before that, you should create a table.
It will be incredibly fast if you use the primary key to search a record or delete a record.
If you want to quit, just input "quit;".
